column5: Sorry, As newb, I did not introduce my self. Basically I been fishing for steelhead for last 12 yrs or so, but not as often as some of you guys.  I got some pics to share (be aware nothing sexy...)  http://img.photobuck.../PICT0162bc.jpg http://img.photobuck...hn/PICT0165.jpg  http://img.photobuck...hn/IMG_3534.jpg
Welcome. I like the last shot.NOBODY, around.
Welcome - nice fish - and one seriously long rod
Welcome aboard. I dunno, those were some pretty sexy pics, if you ask me.

Welcome aboard, you will find the people here are great, very knowledgeable and willing to help a fellow angler. Just don't mention salmon and marshmallows in the same sentence and you should do just fine!  BTW nice pics, I like the action shot!  Daryl

It is always nice to have the river just for myself.. it was not the case in the pic...I just happen to show up after everyone has given up..lucky me that day. a run just started coming up. that kept me busy for a good hour.
Lol  Thank you guys for the awesome welcome. I have a good feeling this is a great fishing forum where lot of great fishermen hangout.   Regards
Welcome, with a rod that long how could you not be sexy?
Whats wrong with salmon and marshmallows   thats my go to  BTW nice chromers
Welcome to the board!  Lots of great people here...nice fish by the way!  I gotta get out to some rivers this fall!
Welcome, Kroot  I wonder who your photographer is... whoever it is, I think he needs to spend less time taking pictures of you and more time catching fish lol!  A couple more:      p.-
wow.. nice fish man!... welcome aboard... by the way how long is ur rod!.. I like the last pic, specially how it bend.. welcome!
I did not mention that Paulus is my personal Photographer. You are welcome to view many more pics in his blog.
Thanks for the comment.  the one above with the spinning reel is a 12'6", the top one with the center pin is a 13'  Cheers
